               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Jones_48-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 9r-140v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_89028232">Geoffrey of Monmouth</author>
                     <title key="work_1677">Historia regum Britanniae</title>
                     <note>Ending abruptly, the last leaves being lost, at lib. x, § 10 'quibus meliores pre.' Text lost between fol. 44v (section 51) and 45r (section 68). See Crick for details of the text.</note>
                     <note>The scribe has added grammatical verses in some of the lower margins (fol. 9r, 'irritat euacuat ...', fol. 17r 'tempus non timpus ...')</note>
                     <note>Fols. iii-viii are medieval endleaves, not apparently in original order or position, blank except for <foreign>ex libris</foreign> (see provenance) and 15th-century note on the origin of the world (fol. 6r)</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
              
               
